  "text": "In Vitro Osteogenic and Adipogenic differentiation. For adipogenic differentiation, hMSCs were recovered after incubation with ILCSs and incubated in appropriated adipogenic differentiation medium (Lonza) [CITATION_1] . The medium was changed two times per week for 3 weeks. The cells were fixed with 10% formalin for 20 min at room temperature and stained with 0.5% Oil Red O (Sigma) in methanol for 20 min at room temperature. For osteogenic differentiation, hMSCs were incubated in osteogenic differentiation medium (Lonza) [CITATION_2] . The media was changed two times per week for 3 weeks. Then cells were fixed with 10% formalin for 20 min at room temperature and stained with Alizarin Red, pH 4.1 (Sigma) for 20 min at room temperature. Images of undifferentiated or differentiated cells were acquired at 20× magnification.",
